title: My Country
author: SpeedyJustice
pages:
#- My country is a symbol, when I was a young man it was a symbol of hope. Even though we lost so much so many times, we came back and proved that we deserved our
spot here on this server.

I came to my country a naive yet hopeful young man, as it was
#- hope that defined our nation in those days.

I assimilated myself here, and became an Icenian. As I grew and developed myself from a citizen to political activist, my country grew and changed alongside me.

I watched as my country turned from 
#- a symbol of hope that inspired the world to fight back against the
forces of evil to a beaurocracy complacent with its role as world babysitter.

I was a naive young man, I fought for change within a system that was fundamentally broken.

#- When I rallied for change and secured my parties interest in the senate through blowout election after blowout, I was only met with pushback from the shadowcouncil that really runs this country.

I was told my vison was too radical, that the people of Icenia
#- cannot be incharge of their own government. That democracy was incompatible with the Icenian way of life, that we were not falling behind and our ways of doing things would carry us through our post war reality.

I ask you my fellow country men and
#- women, have our leaders carried on those same values of hope and change we once carried?

Are you sick of hearing how democracy cannot work as we watch democracies blossom all around us, steal our talent and new blood? Are we really
#- living as we drag our feet directionless on the land we've conqured? 

With all our militaristic victories against our enemies, have we grown from them? As our reputation sinks to new lows every day with each absent minded executive decision met with more
#- and more embarasment can we really celebrate our victories?

Our leadership has promised us that the system works, that we are winning, that this is what victory feels like?

Our brightest have seemingly left our 
#-  country. If they have not left Icenia in its entirity, they have left to form states where they can attempt to distance themselves from the concequences of our leadership.

Statehood is not the solution to our problems, like many other proposed fixes
#- it is simply a band-aid over a bullet wound. 

Our identity as Icenians has been tarnished by those with power who act on our behalf. When we are not oursourcing our free will to the greater ASN alliance, we are putting our reputation on the line of men who have
#- only caused it to suffer. Our powerful military which can conqure any land cannot even counqure a reddit post without a bombardment of hatred and mockery.

How long must we be complacent, suffer through this embarasment in the name of tradition? 
#- When will we stop being afraid of democracy and accept that the old ways of doing things has left us with land we fight tooth and nail to protect yet is no longer worth protecting?

Icenia needs drastic democratic reforms, we cannot sit out this new age of activity
#- with our hands behind our backs waiting for our unelected leadership to make another poor decision and scare them all away.

We are a zombie nation, we've focused so much on fighting and protecting that we have not stopped to ask what exactly it is
#- we are fighting for.

I do not believe our country should go without leadership, but I do believe that our system prevents us from having a truly reresentative government.

Our leadership should represent the best of us, not the worst. 
#- The words of our leaders should reflect the views of our people, not a council of elites who have not logged in to play in months, sometimes years.

The time is now to mobalize as one people, Icenians, around the cause of democracy. We will be
#- hit with criticisms about our competency, "How will you make the trains run on time? How will you keep our factories working?"

We must fight by educating ourselves on how to handle these things. Our battles will not be fought with swords and bows, it will be won
#- with pickaxes and ballots. Prove our critics wrong, pick up an axe or a shovel and do the work they claim we cannot replace.

The time for a democratic revolution was yesterday. The time for you to participate is now, so we may build the
#- future of tommorow.

Share this book with your friends, teach them how to get involved, alone we are weak but together we are strong. We are not statesmen, we are Icenians first and foremost. We must engage in the difficult task of repairing that reputation one good
#- deed at a time.
#- 